class CFunction
extends OSLib

This class is an helper class to generate any call to any WINAPI C-function pointer. (__stdcall on Windows, __cdecl on CE). To issue a given call you have 2 or eventually 3 step to follow.

  1. you should call Prepare with the correct function pointer and the stack size of all arguments. use IntPtr.Size to have size of pointer
  2. then call your C-function pointer with the corresponding Call(..) static method.
  3. eventually, if it is not already implemented, you will have to create your Call method.
To summarize use it like this: 
IntPtr fct = GL.GetProc("glArrayElementEXT");
CFunction.Prepare(fct, 4);
CFunction.Call(1);

Prepare

public static void Prepare( IntPtr pWINAPIFunction, int stacksize );
the most important call before the call itself. prepare the function to be called.
Parameters:
cfunction - the C-function pointer to be called. should follow WINAPI call type (i.e. __stdcall on window, __cdecl on CE)
stacksize - the stack size of all arguments. use IntPtr.Size to find out pointer/array stack size. and use the StackSize function to calculate it.

StackSize

public static int StackSize( params int[] elemSize );
return the stack size for a list of argument of given size. Here I assume that each element occupy an integral number of times the size of one register on the stack and that element bigger than a register simple get cut among as many register as needed, but no more. And that the size of a register is equal to IntPtr.Zero.
Parameters:
elemSize - the size of each element
